We are given an array of integers with condition that if 2 integers are travelling in opposite direstion they collide.
so if given input = [-1 , 1] both of these are travelling in opposite direction so they collide at some point. Note All asteriods travel with same speed.

When a pair of astroids collide there are two scenarios that can happen 

if both are of same size then they explode
if one is bigger and one is smaller , smaller one will explode.



Algorithm:

Step 1: Initialize a stack
Step 2: start looping through the input array:
                      Check if stack is empty and if top of the stack > 0 and if asteroid > 0
                          if(top of stack is less then absolute value of asteroid: the pop stack as smaller one is destroid
                          else if both are equal then both are destroid break out
                          else current asteroid is smaller so it explodes
            if asteroid is not destroid add it to the stack
step 3: add the stack backwards to the array 
step 4: return the result array.


import java.util.*;

class Solution {
    public int[] asteroidCollision(int[] asteroids) {

        Stack<Integer> stack = new Stack<>();

        for (int asteroid : asteroids) {

            boolean destroyed = false;

            while (!stack.isEmpty() && stack.peek() > 0 && asteroid < 0) {

                if (stack.peek() < Math.abs(asteroid)) {
                    // Stack top asteroid is smaller, so it explodes.
                    stack.pop();
                } 
                else if (stack.peek() == Math.abs(asteroid)) {
                    // Both asteroids explode.
                    stack.pop();
                    destroyed = true;
                    break;
                } 
                else {
                    // Current asteroid explodes.
                    destroyed = true;
                    break;
                }
            }

            // Push only if the current asteroid survived.
            if (!destroyed) {
                stack.push(asteroid);
            }
        }

        int[] result = new int[stack.size()];

        // Stack pops in reverse order, so fill result from right to left.
        for (int i = result.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            result[i] = stack.pop();
        }

        return result;
    }
}
